description: For sale: $650,000. Mountaintop living on Minnesota's North Shore! The home was designed by Minnesota architect David Salmela, internationally known for his artful marriage of modernist and traditional Scandinavian forms. The home is anchored to ledge rock and rests on a 6.7 acre ridge top lot with unparalleled views of Lake Superior and the wild country of Tettegouche State Park. Lofty Red Pines crown the lot and a nice mix of Boreal Forest surrounds the home. Finish materials are all of the finest quality. Light pours into the home, a defining characteristic of all Salmela homes. Very private and quiet locale. The home is being sold for a fraction of the cost to build it. The seller will provide a list of repairs and improvements needed to dial the home in for its next owners. The rugged mountainous setting, and a home that comes with some projects, is not for the feint of heart. The next owners like a challenge. They enjoy the natural and wild county of the North Shore and place a premium on high quality design and finish materials.  Above all, the new owners have kept in mind an ideal, pursuing a long held dream of finding a home in a pristine setting, thoughtfully laid out, with all the modern comforts, artfully appointed, and away from everything in this rush and hurry world. This is that place: the modern version of the mountain lodge built on the pick of the litter lot!

description: For sale: $589,000. Amazing Lake Superior Home with a Beach House sitting on the water's edge. This home is all about Lake views - 5 rooms are Lake facing!  The main home features a roomy Four Season porch with knotty-pine entry, large enough for to unload coats, gear and shoes! Beautifully updated kitchen with center island, open to the dining area with cozy bay window allowing lots of natural light to flow inside. Welcoming family room has a wood burning stone fireplace to take away seasonal chills.  Walk out to the large lake side deck, A magical space to enjoy the views while relaxing at your Lake Superior home! All bathrooms have been completely updated, including in floor heat. There is a mini Master Suite on the main level with private full bathroom. Two additional bedrooms, one with access to the deck, and a bathroom complete the package! You and your guests will enjoy the sunrises and sunsets from the deck while mesmerized by the changing colors of Lake Superior. Original hardwood floors in the living room and natural wood work, soft carpet throughout the bedrooms. Gorgeous maple staircase leads to the lower level with a family room and spacious Master Suite. The Master suite has its own fireplace and bathroom with 2 sinks and walk in closet! The lower level also has the laundry room and utility room. Sure, this is a lovely home, but wait until you see The Beach House! Fall in love with the lake views and sounds of the waves from his sweet cottage by the Big Lake! Completely renovated, only one original wall was kept and the loft was added. Nice wood burning fireplace and electric baseboard heat. Enjoy the Lake and S'mores at the bon fire area. With Gorgeous pines and the paved circle drive, the property is fabulously landscaped. Located just an hour North of Duluth and only 30 minutes from Lutsen Mountains Ski area and Superior National Golf Course! Tettegouche State Park is just a few minutes away. What more can you ask for in your Lake Superior home away from home? 100 ft of accessible shoreline, guest cottage, two car garage...all at a great price.

For sale: $1,175,000. Imagine your own classic North-woods lodge in a state park-like setting. This 5800 square foot - 8 bedroom - custom built log estate is situated on 32 incredibly serene and secluded wooded acres. A spectacularly picturesque quarter mile stretch of the Baptism River is yours on both banks. Cast your line for rainbow and speckled trout. Skinny dip in your own private "swimming hole." Create your own personal spur trail to the Red Dot/Moose Walk snowmobile system as it skirts the NW corner of your property. After the snow melts, hike it to Tettegouche State Park and the Superior Hiking Trail. You will share your new property with fox, snowshoe hare, deer and the occasional moose, to mention just a few of your new wild neighbors. This home is situated just 3 minutes up the hill from Minnesota's Lake Superior North Shore and borders Tettegouche State Park to the west and Finland State Forest to the east. This impressive structure combines authentic Norway Pine log beauty with the integrity, stability and insulating advantages of 2x6 framed construction. Perched in a clearing high above the river, the large windows and high ceilings allow natural lighting to flood the home's interior and reveal breathtaking landscape vistas in all directions. There's a huge deck and screened porch overlooking the river, perfect for that big family summer barbecue. With 8 bedrooms, 7 bathrooms, a large laundry room, an office/guest room, modern kitchen, 2 dining and 3 living areas, this would make an ideal family retreat. And zoning even allows for 3 additional riverfront structures. The upper level includes 3 spacious bedrooms and an expansive master suite with Vermont Castings stove. All 4 include custom ensuite bathrooms with jetted tubs and 3 have private balconies. Comfortable and casual up north decor features cedar trim, reclaimed hemlock floors, log beams and custom ceramic tile throughout. This estate was designed with the utmost attention to every detail and the result is a feast for the senses. Three large living areas - including 2 with stone fireplaces - can be utilized to suit the new owner's needs. Built with energy conservation in mind and comfortable in-floor heat throughout. Completely hardwired for TV, phone, in ceiling stereo speakers and high-speed fiber optic internet. Your investment is protected by interconnected smoke detectors, whole house surge protection and a whole house fire sprinkler system. High quality furnishings are included for almost all the entire main and upper living areas. Also includes a large detached metal storage building with full electrical service and 2 zones of pex tubing installed in the slab. Today it's lots of extra storage space. Tomorrow perhaps a heated garage, woodworking shop or even a bunkhouse for the kids. For the final "up north" touch, a whimsical Finish sauna is tucked in the woods between your retreat and the river. Out of sugar? Restock at Finland's 100-year-old historic co-op, only 3 minutes away. You owe it to yourself to view this extraordinary property in-person. (2.5% commission paid to buyer's agent)
